<ul>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Level progression: end a map when a certain condition is met (acquire object, reach checkpoint, destroy enemies) and load the next one. Would give potential for complex games and missions.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Ninja rope that latches on to other worms, like in Liero.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> The option for collectible power ups during gameplay, especially health.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> An option within the <acronym title="Graphical User Interface">GUI</acronym> to play without blood and gore.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> STEERABLES!!!! (eg the missile) they&#039;re an integral part of liero</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Option to disable weapon comboing.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> More of a <acronym title="Graphical User Interface">GUI</acronym>.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Water, and being able to change the colour of it.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Objects with sprites that can block worms like rock.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Multiple layers of Paralax.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Default mod to be updated, since no-one ever plays any other mods.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> More weapons in the default mod.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Third hotseat player.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> More Structured games (e.g. deathmatch, tag, ctf, etc.)</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> CTF Flags a part of maps, instead of just randomly appearing (as in old Liero) (Think First Person Shooter CTF)</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Vehicles (enabled/chosen/disabled by host pre gamestart)</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Health Handicaps</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Player colour changer in the <acronym title="Graphical User Interface">GUI</acronym></div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Ability to change controls in <acronym title="Graphical User Interface">GUI</acronym></div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Pause game feature (so you can walk away from the bots for a moment if needed)</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Bots able/know how to dig (they always seem to get stuck)</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Mouse aim control (like in Soldat)</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> ebuild for Gentoo users (see this bug: <a href="http://bugs.gentoo.org/143322" class="urlextern" title="http://bugs.gentoo.org/143322"  rel="nofollow">http://bugs.gentoo.org/143322</a>)</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Source Releases? (Release .tar.gz archives of the source with each release?)</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> ninja rope that interact with terrain and the ability to lengthen/shorten thru button commands.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Weapon crates (as in old Liero)</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Ability to easily change loading times for all weapons (as in old Liero)</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Bouncing projectiles(eg. bouncy larpa,bouncy mine)</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Floating projectiles(eg. float mine)</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> <acronym title="Graphical User Interface">GUI</acronym>-Option to change Worm HP as in old Liero</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Minimap where you can see where the other worms are (like in original Liero)</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Blood should not disappear, it should remain on the ground (like in original Liero) :)</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Frag limit</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Sniper window - opens when using laser sighted weapon, shows, what&#039;s at the end of laser line :)</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> ability to use more/less weapons (from 1 to 20 for ex)</div>
</li>
